    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#State</IRI>
        <Literal>From Karray et al. 2019:

A BFO:Process in which some BFO:independent continuant endures and one or more of the dependent entities it bears does not change in kind or intensity</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#StateOfFailure</IRI>
        <Literal>Commento Chiara/Ada:

physical failure non ci serve! non facciamo manutenzione quanto una cosa è rotta pèerchè è rotta, ma perchè non fa più la funzione richiesta

TBN: lo stato in cui è fisicamente rotto sarà da modellare, ma non come failure, quanto come una situazione in cui l&apos;asset è</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#StateOfFailure</IRI>
        <Literal>From Karray et al. 2019:

A ROM:state during which a CCO:artifact is unable to perform its BFO:function</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Tool</IRI>
        <Literal>From IOF:

An Artifact that is designed to assist in the performance of manual or mechanical work and not to be consumed in that process

TBR</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#TriggeringEvent</IRI>
        <Literal>From Karray et al. 2019:
A BFO:process resulting in an action.

From Montero et al. 2021:
A BFO: process boundary that is the starting point for a maintenance action</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
